# URL do projeto Supabase (ex: https://xxxxx.supabase.co)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here

# Chave p√∫blica/anon do projeto Supabase
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# =====================================================
# How to Configure (Developers Only):
# =====================================================
# 1. Create a free account at https://supabase.com
# 2. Create a new project in the Supabase dashboard
# 3. Execute the SQL scripts:
#    - First: supabase-setup.sql
#    - Then: supabase-auth-migration.sql
# 4. Get your credentials from: Settings > API
#    - Project URL: paste into VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#    - anon public key: paste into VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# 5. For local development:
#    - Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
#    - Replace the values above with your credentials
#    - Restart the server: npm run dev
# 6. For production (Vercel):
#    - Configure the variables in the Vercel panel
#    - Settings > Environment Variables
#
# ‚ö†Ô∏è IMPORTANT: 
# - Use the "anon" (public) key, NOT the "service_role" (private) key
# - This configuration enables all users to access the system
# - Each user will have their own isolated tournaments
#
# üìñ Full guide: DEVELOPER_SETUP.md

